Edna Mae Harris https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edna_Mae_Harris 0 Edna Mae Harris (September 29, 1914 – September 15, 1997), sometimes credited as Edna May Harris was an American actress and singer. Harris was one of the premier African–American film actress of the late 1930s and early 1940s, appearing in films featuring mostly African–American casts.
